name: 福星海鲜 FU Xing Seafood

reviews.text:
Looking at the last few reviews from 7 months before which were mostly negative and seeing the steady flow of people ordering from the stall, thought will give it a try.

Ordered assam fish head and fried egg with chives. Assam fish head which costs $25 is ok, with nothing exceptional or bad. What irks me is the fried egg with chives. At $8, I would have expected something more substantial than what you can see from the photo. My kids feel that it’s only worth $3 but I think $5 is probably reasonable. Definitely not $8. While it tastes ok, this has marred the experience and one try is more than enough for us.

On 11 Aug 24 around 2040hr, order a yee mee. As shown in a photo given 3 or 4 pcs of vege cut in 1/4, pork slices is dry and the food sucks. Not going to patronise this stall again. Never check Google reviews before dining and after checking the reviews is bad.

Tried their white bee hoon today. Not worth for the price.
Only 5 small clams, 2 medium prawns, and a few pcs of cabbage in a STICKY GRAVY.

However compared to other hawkers, $6 of white bee hoon got squids, clams, eggs, cabbage with a super fresh soup.

Order a total of $244 worth of food on cny 2022 day 2

Cereal prawn cost $70 for 8 PCs. LOL knife too sharp already.
Food are really good and of reasonable price. Dinning area are specious. Will definitely be back for more.. Well done Fu Xing!!
